verbs.description: typecast (third-person singular simple present typecasts, present participle typecasting, simple past and past participle typecast or typecasted)

entries.meaning: (acting) To cast an actor in the same kind of role repeatedly.
To identify one as being of a specific type because of one's appearance, colour, religion etc.
(programming) To cast (change of data type of a variable or object).
examples: Does anyone know how to typecast a String in Java into an int?

entries.meaning: (printing, historical) To found type in a mold.
